Package: exportreg
Title: Regression Table Exporter for Applied Economists
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: person("Vicente", "LR", role = c("aut", "cre"),
    email = "fill@in.example")
Description: Produces formatted regression tables for export to Excel
    and LaTeX, with first-class support for fixest models. Designed for
    applied economists who need publication-ready tables from feols(),
    lm(), felm(), and ivreg() models.
License: MIT + file LICENSE
Encoding: UTF-8
Roxygen: list(markdown = TRUE)
RoxygenNote: 7.3.3
Depends:
    R (>= 4.1.0)
Imports:
    fixest,
    broom,
    openxlsx2
Suggests:
    lfe,
    AER,
    testthat (>= 3.0.0),
    knitr,
    rmarkdown
Config/testthat/edition: 3
VignetteBuilder: knitr
